GENERAL INFORMATION
AIRPORT CHECK IN TIMES
To help us give you better service and on time departures, you should be
at the airport a minimum of
(30) thirty minutes for flights within Canada
(45) forty five minutes for flights to Seattle
before flight departure.
Should you require special handling, eg. wheelchair, or checking an unusual
piece of baggage, please allow extra time.
Failure to be present at the Boarding Gate at least (10) ten minutes prior to
scheduled departure time may result in cancellation and ineligibility for denied
boarding compensation.
BAGGAGE
(All baggage must be labeled with the passenger's name). Fragile items
accepted only when properly packaged. Perishable items accepted only when
properly packaged and checked as a separate piece of baggage. Money,
jewelery, silverware, negotiable papers, securities, samples and liquids are not
acceptable in or as part of checked baggage at any time.
Restricted articles such as firearms, ammunition, matches, compressed gases,
corrosive acids, flammable liquids and solids, mercury, radio-active materials
are either prohibited entirely or may only be carried by prior arrangement.
Check with AirBC for further details.
BAGGAGE ALLOWANCE
AirBC Airport Service (40 lbs)
18 kgs
AirBC Harbour Service (25 lbs) 11.5 kgs
Excess baggage may be accepted space permitting.
Extra charges will apply.
TARIFFS AND LIABILITY
Fares, Schedules and other information published herein are subject to change
without notice. AirBC will not be responsible for damages resulting from failure
of aircraft to depart or arrive at times stated herein. AirBC is only liable to the
extent shown in its current tariffs published and filed pursuant to law and
available for public inspection at the Head Office at AirBC.

HARBOUR TERMINALS
Vancouver Harbour - 1/2 Blocks East of Bayshore Inn
Victoria Harbour - Adjacent to Empress Hotel
CREDIT CARDS
AirBC accepts EnRoute and other major credit cards for transportation charges.
AIR CARGO
Carried on all AirBC flights.
